<h1>Angel Food Dessert</h1>
<img src="https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/previews/054/361/120/non_2x/delicious-sponge-cake-with-fresh-berries-and-whipped-cream-free-photo.jpg">
<ul>
<li>1 (10 inch) angel food cake</li>
<li>2 (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, softened</li>
<li>1 cup white sugar</li>
<li>1 (8 ounce) container frozen whipped topping, thawed</li>
<li>1 quart fresh strawberries, sliced</li>
<li>1 (18 ounce) jar strawberry glaze</li>

</ul>
<h3>Directions</h3>
    <p>Gather all ingredients. </p>
    <p>Crumble or cut cake into bite-sized pieces. Arrange in a 9x13-inch dish. </p>
    <p>Beat cream cheese and sugar in a medium bowl until light and fluffy. Fold in whipped topping. </p>
    <p>Press cake down to form a layer. Spread cream cheese mixture over cake layer. </p>
    <p>Combine strawberries and glaze in a bowl until strawberries are evenly coated. </p>
    <p>Spread over cream cheese layer. </p>
    <p>Chill until it is ready to serve.</p>
